dct_title_s: Map showing the line of mean high water of the westerly channel of the Passaic River, also known as the "slank"
dct_description_sm: Map of Dundee Island Park and adjacent streets along the Passaic River, with mean high water lines from 1894 and 1912
Source map supplied by New Jersey Department of Environmental Protection
As shown upon an assessment map of the first ward of the city of Passaic, made by Wise and Watson Surveyors May 20th, 1894, showing encroachments upon said westerly channel by survey of January 1912
